  <name>OpenDCS</name>
  <summary>Distributed Control System Components</summary>

  <description>
    <_p>
      OpenDCS is a set of applications and services to design and use
      distributed control systems for data acquisition and control.
      Libraries for all core functionality and a libpeas plugins framework
      are provided to extend what is possible. Additionally, the core
      services use ZeroMQ as a message queue, a RESTful interface, and
      DBus calls to make it possible to communicate with them in any
      language that can communicate in these ways.
    </_p>
    <_p>Features:</_p>
    <ul>
      <_li>Configurable UI through XML</_li>
      <_li>Configurable data acquisition services through XML</_li>
      <_li>Configurable data logging services through XML</_li>
      <_li>Configurable feedback control services through XML</_li>
      <_li>Plugin system to simplify adding support for measurement devices</_li>
      <_li>Plugin system to simplify adding support for new data logging backends</_li>
    </ul>
  </description>

